I need this app hosted on Expo servers using the current, supported EAS Update workflow. No tunnel mode. No deprecated commands.

Do the following steps in order and stop only when EAS Update is working.
	1.	Check the local Expo CLI version.
	•	If the project is using an old global expo-cli, remove it.
	•	Ensure the modern Expo CLI (expo) is installed and being used.
	•	Confirm expo --version is 6.x or higher.
	2.	Verify the project root.
	•	Confirm package.json and app.json or app.config.ts exist.
	•	Abort if not in the correct directory.
	3.	Ensure the user is logged into Expo.
	•	Run expo whoami.
	•	If not logged in, prompt to log in with expo login.
	4.	Install the OTA updates package.
	•	Install expo-updates using npx expo install expo-updates.
	5.	Configure Expo Updates correctly.
	•	Open app.json or app.config.ts.
	•	Ensure it includes:
	•	a valid name
	•	a valid slug
	•	updates.fallbackToCacheTimeout = 0
	•	runtimeVersion set to { policy: "sdkVersion" }
	•	Do not remove existing valid config.
	6.	Initialize EAS for the project.
	•	Run npx expo prebuild --clean.
	•	Allow generation of native folders and configuration.
	7.	Verify EAS is enabled.
	•	Run npx expo doctor.
	•	Fix any blocking errors related to updates or configuration.
	8.	Publish the app to Expo servers using the supported command.
	•	Run npx expo update --message "Initial release".
	9.	Confirm success.
	•	Ensure an update ID is returned.
	•	Confirm the project is now accessible via the Expo project URL.
	•	Confirm it can be opened in Expo Go without the local dev server running.